  "prompt": "What are some small restaurant chains in Dallas? (under 10 locations)",
  "response": "Dallas is home to several small restaurant chains with under 10 locations that offer a variety of cuisines and dining experiences. Here are a few notable ones:\n\n1. **Taco y Vino**\n   - **Locations:** 2\n   - **Cuisine:** Mexican and wine bar\n   - **Description:** A cozy spot offering a unique blend of Mexican cuisine and an extensive wine selection. Perfect for a casual yet sophisticated dining experience.\n\n2. **The Porch**\n   - **Locations:** 3\n   - **Cuisine:** American comfort food\n   - **Description:** Known for its Southern comfort food, The Porch offers a relaxed atmosphere with a menu featuring dishes like chicken fried steak and homemade mac and cheese.\n\n3. **Whistle Britches**\n   - **Locations:** 3\n   - **Cuisine:** Southern comfort food\n   - **Description:** Specializing in fried chicken and comfort sides, Whistle Britches brings a taste of the South with a modern twist. It's a great spot for family dining.\n\n4. **Taco Stop**\n   - **Locations:** 4\n   - **Cuisine:** Mexican\n   - **Description:** A local favorite for quick and delicious tacos, Taco Stop offers a variety of fresh, made-to-order options that are perfect for a casual meal.\n\n5. **The Henry**\n   - **Locations:** 2\n   - **Cuisine:** American comfort food\n   - **Description:** Known for its all-day breakfast and comfort food menu, The Henry is a popular spot for both locals and visitors looking for a hearty meal in a friendly environment.\n\n6. **Y.O. Ranch Steakhouse**\n   - **Locations:** 2\n   - **Cuisine:** Steakhouse\n   - **Description:** A classic steakhouse offering a variety of premium steaks and a rustic atmosphere, perfect for a special occasion or a hearty meal.\n\nThese small chains are beloved by locals and offer a range of dining experiences from casual to upscale, making them great options to explore in Dallas.",
